<br />Unless the game is structured so that only the code is free software, and the data that the program uses (tiles, maps, sound effects, music) is under a non-free license. In fact, I seem to remember a commercial total conversion of the GPL version of id Tech 3 (the Quake III Arena engine) distributed as an "aggregate" consisting of a free program and non-free data in the same package, which is explicitly allowed by the GPL.</div>

